# Agent Memory

Read `docs/agent-memory.md` at the start of every substantial task, but use
only the entries relevant to the current request.

When the chat contains durable project knowledge, update `docs/agent-memory.md` in the same change:

- User preferences that should apply again later
- Architecture or product decisions
- Important commands, environment notes, or operational gotchas
- Repeated constraints or things to avoid
- Open questions that should not be lost

Memory hygiene matters: too much irrelevant context can cause hallucination.
Do not add transient status updates, secrets, raw credentials, raw chat
transcripts, speculative interpretations, or one-off implementation details.
If a detail affects future agent behavior, add it under the most relevant
section with the date and keep it to one short bullet.
